            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "After a while, I think this behavior is correct. It prevents a class of bug where the channel id is reused but a stale one is held elsewhere before cleanup occurs (ie. in a dict).\r\n\r\nThere should probably be documentation to remind users that they have to close the channel once they're done with it. I believe I got the assumption that the channel auto closes from [`:h channel_buffered`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/channel.html#channel-buffered).\r\n\r\n> `channel-buffered` The callback is invoked immediately as data is available, where a single-item list `['']` indicates EOF (stream closed).",
            "created_at": "2023-02-04T06:14:50Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/11166#issuecomment-1416674818",
