            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The current behavior is inconsistent. If the channel is an RPC channel, it is closed automatically:\n```vim\n:echo sockconnect('tcp', 'localhost:8000', {'rpc': v:true})\n```\n\n> It prevents a class of bug where the channel id is reused but a stale one is held elsewhere before cleanup occurs (ie. in a dict).\n\nThere is no such kind of reuse.",
